<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>It's the stuff of dreams for Shamrock Rovers as they face Serie A outfit AC Milan in the second round of Europa League qualifying tonight.</p>

<p>Shamrock are hoping to pull off what would be an absolutely incredible victory against Zlatan Ibrahimovic and Co at the Tallaght Stadium.</p>

<p>And Ibrahimovic and his Milan team-mates have taken to the field against the Irish minnows - whose whole squad value is dwarfed by Swedish legend Ibrahimovic.</p>

<p>Zlatan Ibrahimovic leaps in the air during the early stages against Shamrock Rovers</p>

<p>Ibrahimovic warms up ahead of AC Milan's clash at Shamrock Rovers tonight</p>

<p>Milan boss Stefano Pioli will be desperate to avoid a massive shock against the Irish minnows</p>

<p>Ahead of the match, Shamrock boss Stephen Bradley said his players are relishing the opportunity to come up against one of Europe's old elite clubs.</p>

<p>Bradley said: 'The bigger the game, the bigger the occasion, the better these players are.</p>

<p>'They've grown together as a group and in the last 12-14 months they've shown the bigger the game, the better they are. They want to perform.</p>

<p>'We're under no illusions how difficult it will be, but there's a stage there and I genuinely feel the players will perform.</p>

<p>'The pitch looks fantastic, we're playing one of the biggest clubs in the world with great players - it's time to enjoy it, perform and do what we do.'</p>

<p>More to follow... </p>

<p>Shamrock Rovers players warm up ahead of a huge European night for the Irish club</p>
